Sentencas: A novel cobalt-free perovskite La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3 - delta (LBFN) powder was synthesized using a combustion method.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase composition, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), and electrochemical properties of LBFN were systematically investigated.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction (XRD) results revealed that LBFN had a high chemical compatibility with Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 - delta (SDC).
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LBFN cathode exhibited a competitive electrode area-specific resistance (ASR) for the symmetric cell based on SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the electrochemical performance of LBFN cathode could be effectively improved with the addition of the proper amount of SDC.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using the LBFN-SDC73 (7:3 in weight ratio) as a composite cathode, the Ni-SDC-supported single cell with a 25-mu m-thick SDC electrolyte exhibited maximum power densities of 330, 216, and 119 mW cm(-2) at 600, 550, and 500 A degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization and performance of cobalt-free perovskite-type La0.6Ba0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
